FAQs on Study in Georgia and Study Medicine in Georgia
Why should I consider studying in Georgia?
Studying in Georgia offers high-quality education, affordable tuition fees, and a rich cultural experience. The country has a welcoming environment for international students and offers numerous programs taught in English.

Are degrees from Georgian universities recognized internationally?
Yes, degrees from Georgian universities are recognized internationally. Graduates are eligible to sit for international licensing exams, such as the USMLE and PLAB, which allow them to practice medicine worldwide.

What is the cost of living in Georgia for students?
The cost of living in Georgia is relatively low compared to many Western countries. Students can expect to spend between $300 to $500 per month on accommodation, food, transportation, and other living expenses.
